
/*
 * 1. The [get-value] slot is used to retrieve the value of the node specified by the expression `:x:@.arguments/*/offset`.
 * 2. The expression navigates to the [offset] node within the children of the [.arguments] node and extracts its value.
 * 
 * Use cases:
 * - Fetching the user-provided [offset] argument in a paginated API endpoint.
 * - Accessing an [offset] parameter to determine where to start processing a collection or data stream.
 * - Pulling the [offset] value to implement custom business logic that depends on a numeric offset, such as skipping a number of records in a result set.
 */
get-value:x:@.arguments/*/offset
